h2. Issue Summary
When users are uploading an attachment on the Fabric editor, the media upload detecting a file which is uploading to the Fabric editor which cause the publish button *greyed* out intermittently and created an empty file card which pointing to the attachment. 

This due to the asynchronous nature of media uploads happening on uploading a huge file to the Fabric editor. When users trying to publish the content, they will see the publish button greyed out since the editor "detecting" a file that is uploading to our media server. Closing the editor and re-enter the edit mode once again, the file card is created on the page. But the file wasn't physically existed on the page. 

*Note*: This is also happening to some images file which less file size.  There're some reported cases whereby the attachment was embedded on the page for a few days but disappears from Media server. 

h4. Screenshot of the Error
 !screenshot-1.png|thumbnail! 

h2. Error from the Browser Console
{code}
{"error":{"code":"NotFoundError","title":"The file with the given id does not have any binary content","href":"https://api.media.atlassian.com#NotFoundError"}}{code}
h2. Splunk logs from Media API
{code}
message:	 Could not find data for attachment: Attachment: Schermafdruk 2019-03-19 19.28.06.png v.1 (524779558) marc.blekkink - com.atlassian.confluence.pages.persistence.dao.filesystem.AttachmentDataFileSystemException: Cannot get attachment data for attachment 524779558 from Media because Failure{cause=org.codehaus.jackson.JsonParseException: Cannot find child node with name:artifacts, reason=TRANSPORT_ERROR, message='null', httpStatusCode=null}{code}

Note: The missing attachment also causing timeout GraphQL error:

{code}
"Frontend Version: candidate-407"
"Error: GraphQL error: Timeout error querying the remote graphql service.{code}


h2. Steps to Replicate
This error happens randomly and the steps to replicate it are unknown at this time.

h3. Workaround
* Re-upload the file to the page again.

